  "prompt": "What is the use of microbeads in cosmetics?",
  "response": "Microbeads are tiny plastic spheres that have been used in a variety of cosmetic and personal care products, primarily in exfoliating scrubs, cleansers, and some forms of makeup. Specifically, their purposes include:\n\n1. **Exfoliation**: Microbeads serve as an abrasive agent that helps to remove dead skin cells, dirt, and oil from the skin. This can leave the skin feeling smoother and looking brighter.\n\n2. **Texture Improvement**: They can enhance the texture of creams, gels, and lotions, providing a smooth feel during application.\n\n3. **Visual Enhancement**: In cosmetics, microbeads can add a glittery or shimmering effect, making products look more appealing.\n\n4. **Thickening Agent**: Microbeads can contribute to the thickness and viscosity of formulations, allowing for better application and feel.\n\nHowever, due to environmental concerns\u2014such as their contribution to ocean pollution and harm to marine life\u2014many countries have begun to restrict or ban the use of microbeads in cosmetics and personal care products. They are being replaced with natural exfoliants (like jojoba beads) or biodegradable alternatives.",
